## Summary

**Nick Offerman → Enneagram Type 9 (Peacemaker), 9w1, Social/one-to-one.**

- **Core tension:** TV's most emotionally sealed icon (Ron Swanson) is, in life, a hugger and a weeper who disappears into things quieter than himself — a character, a marriage, a workbench.
- **Hook:** the 30-minute sob when he got the Ron Swanson call ("years and years of repressed feeling from never getting the big shot").
- **Empathy turn:** the "folksy craftsman is just a brand" skeptic, reframed by the timeline — Offerman Woodshop was founded in 2001, eight years before fame, in poverty. The sanctuary came first; the brand followed.
- **Citation-grade stat:** Type 9s are 21 of 134 film/TV figures in the 9takes corpus (~16% vs ~10% catalog-wide).
- **Furniture:** drop cap, TL;DR accordion, inner-thought (interior beat), contrast-panel (Ron vs Nick), pull-quote, and the required Enneagram Rabbit Hole (wing, subtype, arrows, counterarguments).

